Function Reference/image make intermediate size « WordPress Codex
-----------

Resize an image to make a thumbnail or intermediate size.

The returned array has the file size, the image width, and image height.
The filter 'image\_make\_intermediate\_size' can be used to hook in and
change the values of the returned array. The only parameter is the
resized file path.

Usage
-----

` <?php image_make_intermediate_size( $file, $width, $height, $crop ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$file` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) File path.
    Default: *None*

 `$width` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Image width.
    Default: *None*

 `$height` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Image height.
    Default: *None*

 `$crop` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional, default is false. Whether to crop image to
    specified height and width or resize.
    Default: false

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(boolean|array)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   False, if no image was created. Metadata array on success.

Change Log
----------

Since: [2.5](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

Source File
-----------

`image_make_intermediate_size()` is located in `wp-includes/media.php`

